The signing of the agreement comes after four months of thorough negotiations within the trade unions. According to Marius Croucamp, Deputy General Secretary of Solidarity s Metal and Engineering Industry, four months of intensive negotiations will be encapsulated tomorrow with the signing of the agreement, Solidarity said in a statement.The agreement will also be signed by the National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa (Numsa), United Association of South Africa (Uasa), Metal and Electrical Workers union of South Africa (Mewusa) and the SA Equity Workers Association (Saewa).